	•	design thinking

5. Rendering is downstream of ontology

We were able to describe the animation before we could render it. That means the deeper asset is not the pixels. It is the structure of what is happening.

That is huge.

Because it means if you have the ontology right:
	•	different renderers can project it
	•	different models can implement it
	•	different media can carry the same event

Same heart, different body.

